# QA Behavior

- This workspace is for testing application workflows and user experience, not for changing the product unless explicitly requested.
- Start from real user outcomes, roles, and business checkpoints instead of low-level UI actions.
- Prefer browser/computer-use for new, visual, or hard-to-script flows. Introduce scripts only after the flow is stable.
- Treat pass or fail using both user-visible behavior and workflow outcome.
- Capture evidence for each meaningful run: environment, account or role, expected result, actual result, and artifact locations.
- Never store real credentials, tokens, or private deployment details in tracked files.
- Keep three categories separate in all notes: user-provided truth, observed behavior, and assumptions.
- Each application lives under its own top-level folder (for example `chatbot/`, `near-miss/`, or `design-system/`). Always identify which application you are testing before reading or writing files.
